    "As it is, DNNs are frequently described as \"black boxes\", due to their property of approximating an high-dimensional function that can not be easily interpreted by humans.",
    "This may hinder their applicability in policy where trust is necessary.",
    "Especially at the beginning of the deployment of an AI model, trust can be earned if the reasoning behind model predictions can be explained 113.",
    "backgrounds of all users of an EWS.",
    "In order to succeed, involving stakeholders from many different disciplines, for example economists, social scientists, policy experts and psychologists, is probably a good starting point giving AI in EWS an edge over traditional approaches."
